		<title>04LOCAL HISTORY (MONUMENTS)</title>
		<content> There are very few historical         
 monuments in the area. At{Mapplewell} 
 there a cross to commemorate the men  
 of the village who died in the two    
 world wars. At {Athersley}there is a  
 monument in the form of a pit landing 
 gear in rememberance of the men who   
 died in the{Carlton Main}pit disaster.
                                       
 On August 6th. 1936 there was a gas   
 explosion killing 58 men from the     
 local area.                           
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
